# рџ¤– Machine Learning Model

**Algorithm**

- Random Forest Regressor

**Target Variable**

- Electricity_Price_EUR

**Input Features**

- Demand_MWh
- Wind_Generation_MWh
- Solar_Generation_MWh
- Gas_Price_EUR
- CO2_Price_EUR
- Temperature_C

---

# рџ“Љ Model Performance

| Metric | Value |
|---------|------:|
| MAE | 4.25 |
| RMSE | 5.27 |
| RВІ Score | 0.705 |

The model explains approximately **70% of the variation** in electricity prices on the test dataset.

---

# рџ§  Feature Importance

| Feature | Importance |
|---------|-----------:|
| Demand_MWh | 60.0% |
| Gas_Price_EUR | 11.5% |
| Solar_Generation_MWh | 11.0% |
| CO2_Price_EUR | 7.6% |
| Wind_Generation_MWh | 6.5% |
| Temperature_C | 3.4% |

The results indicate that electricity demand is the strongest driver of market prices, followed by gas prices and renewable energy generation.

